:2048x1365/2400x1600/filters:focal(1039x617:1040x618):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24979235/Flipper.jpg 2400w" src="https://duet-cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0x0:2048x1365/2400x1600/filters:focal(1039x617:1040x618):format(webp)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24979235/Flipper.jpg"/></noscript></span><div class="duet--media--caption pt-6 font-polysans-mono text-12 font-light leading-130 tracking-1"><figcaption class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline text-gray-13 dark:text-gray-e9 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-black [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-e9 dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-13 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63"><em>It’s the Flipper Zero. Clearly.</em></figcaption> <cite class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline not-italic text-gray-63 dark:text-gray-bd [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-63 [&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a:hover]:shadow-underline-gray [&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray-63 dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:text-gray-bd dark:[&amp;&gt;a]:shadow-underline-gray">Image: Flipper Zero</cite></div></figure></div></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">The Flipper Zero — which the company calls a “portable multi-tool for pentesters and geeks in a toy-like body,” <em>Verge</em> friend Chris Person calls “<a href="/23433594/flipper-zero-hacking-gadget-wireless-pentesting-open-source-antenna">a Swiss Army Knife of antennas</a>,” and my kids call “the meebo” because I use it to emulate Amiibos for them — is now available in a <a href="https://shop.flipperzero.one/products/flipper-zero-transparent">limited edition with a transparent shell</a>. I could have made several sentences from that info, but it felt appropriate to the spirit of Flipper Zero to cram it all into one.</p></div><div class="duet--article--article-body-component"><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup duet--article--standard-paragraph my-12 font-fkroman text-17 leading-150 text-gray-13 selection:bg-franklin-20 dark:text-white dark:selection:bg-blurple [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin dark:[&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-blurple [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-black dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-white">Aside from the casing, the limited-edition translucent model is just like the other Flipper Zero units, with (among other things) RFID, NFC, sub-GHz, Bluetooth, USB-C, and a row of GPIO ports along the top so you can interface with other hardware. In July, the company <a href="/2023/7/24/23803600/flipper-zero-app-store-launch">added an app store</a>, which makes it easier for dilettantes like me to find cool software for the Flipper Zero. </p></div><span class="mb-8 font-polysans text-15 font-medium leading-150 tracking-1 text-gray-13 "><a class="inline-block shadow-underline-black hover:shadow-highlight-franklin" href="/2023/10/5/23904454/flipper-zero-transparent-edition-multitool-hacking">Read Article &gt;</a></span></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-9bc8fff7-6984-435f-9bd5-f122471fb8ee"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box