rple" href="/authors/sean-hollister">Sean Hollister</a></span></p></div></div><div class="font-polysans text-black dark:text-gray-ef leading-150"><div class="inline pr-4 text-17 font-bold md:text-17">Transparent batteries are hot.</div><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup inline font-fkroman text-gray-33 dark:text-gray-ef [&amp;_a]:relative [&amp;_a]:z-10   [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin [&amp;_a]:text-gray-33 [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-gray-33 dark:[&amp;_a]:text-gray-ef dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-franklin">I wouldn’t say they’re <em>practical</em>, but I absolutely love how they look — and the new $59 <a href="https://sharge.com/pages/icemag-landingpage">Icemag</a> even has its own tiny RGB fan. </p><p class="duet--article--dangerously-set-cms-markup mt-12 font-fkroman text-gray-33 dark:text-gray-ef [&amp;_a]:relative [&amp;_a]:z-10   [&amp;_a:hover]:shadow-highlight-franklin [&amp;_a]:text-gray-33 [&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-gray-33 dark:[&amp;_a]:text-gray-ef dark:[&amp;_a]:shadow-underline-franklin">These three batteries are all from Sharge (I think it rhymes with “Charge”) and I can’t wait to see what the Shenzhen company does next. While I don’t own these batteries, I did Kickstart <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/shargetech/sharge-disk-the-ultimate-storage-solution-for-edc-device">its tiny transparent SSD enclosure</a>, where my old Steam Deck drive will hopefully soon live.</p><br/></div><div class="pt-12"><div class="duet--media--embed min-h-[500px] [&amp;&gt;div&gt;iframe]:!min-w-0 quickpost mb-0 w-full relative z-10 overflow-x-hidden md:max-w-full"></div></div></div></div></div></div></li><li role="article" class="mx-[-16px] mb-40 mt-[-40px] px-16 last:mb-0 md:mx-0 md:px-0" id="stream-entry-e4ec3474-0e0a-4b60-bf1f-1d2d5e2983a8"><div class="border-solid border-blurple-df pt-40 sm:border-b-0 border-b"><div class="mb-40"><div class="duet--content-cards--content-card z-10 flex max-w-container-md flex-row border-b border-solid border-gray-cc px-0 last-of-type:border-b-0 dark:border-gray-31"><div class="flex min-w-0 flex-1 flex-col"><div class="mb-10 flex items-center"><div class="absolute left-[-2px] hidden h-6 w-12 border-y-2 border-white bg-[#DFCFFF] md:block"></div><div class="relative mr-8 block h-[36px] w-[36px] flex-none overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-solid border-gray-ef bg-[#DFCFFF]"><span style="box-sizing:border-box;display:block;overflow:hidden;width:initial;height:initial;background:none;opacity:1;border:0;margin:0;padding:0;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0"><img alt="Alex Cranz" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="rounded-full" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover"/><noscript><img alt="Alex Cranz" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;right:0;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0;border:none;margin:auto;display:block;width:0;height:0;min-width:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;max-height:100%;object-fit:cover" class="rounded-full" sizes="36px" srcSet="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7uGyqBSPZaPSs0IPouurJEJwWJ4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/197080/IMG_5483.0.jpg 16w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7uGyqBSPZaPSs0IPouurJEJwWJ4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/197080/IMG_5483.0.jpg 32w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7uGyqBSPZaPSs0IPouurJEJwWJ4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/197080/IMG_5483.0.jpg 48w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7uGyqBSPZaPSs0IPouurJEJwWJ4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/197080/IMG_5483.0.jpg 64w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7uGyqBSPZaPSs0IPouurJEJwWJ4=/512x512/cdn.vox-cdn.com/author_profile_images/197080/IMG_5483.0.jpg 96w, https://